Found this well-hidden gem when looking for the uniquely well hidden Post Office. Both are located in the Aon buiding basement. Having mailed our cards we hit upon this place which is part of a local chain. Point of difference seems to be that the food is 100% antibiotic free. You can eat healthily but still have fun ( you know, it's not that dismal rabbit food sludge). Salad bar has all sorts of salad that you'd make yourself (if you could ever be bothered), also hot entrees, pizza, sandwiches, soups. Lots of choice, I'd recommend it.

They have salads, panini, pizza, and soup, and you can do a combo, too, for under $8. plus tax. I had a salad and half a panini, and both were excellent. And though it was packed during lunch, service was quite speedy. A great spot for breakfast. The food is great and the prices are low. The staff are very friendly and helpful. A great place to have a quiet breakfast before starting your day.

I got the Sweet Life salad for lunch sans golden raisins and it was just fine. The spicy peanuts were an interesting flavor component, but overall toppings were sparse and grilled chicken was served cold (pet peeve of mine if I'm paying >$10 for a salad). Probably won't be back here if I'm looking for a salad.

Stop #235 for @pizzas365: Sopraffina Marketcaffe has a pretty decent (and relatively inexpensive) pizza, with lots of classic options and a couple unique options. The thin crust is good, but has a bit of an odd / plastic-y crunch, and the toppings are all pretty solid. 3.8 Stars.

Where else could you get half a pizza and a "half" salad for under 10 bucks? Either one of them is enough to fill you up. One of the best lunch deals. Plus the staff has been there forever and they're all very nice. It always lifts my heart and satisfies my belly at Sopraffina.
Decent sandwiches. Great for a quick lunch.

The food here is what I would consider average. The advantages to this place are it's quick and convenient to grab lunch. I come here a lot out because it's easy and efficient to get in and out. They serve cafeteria style, so you come in and there are different stations for whatever you want.... soup, salad, pasta, sandwiches, etc. I have tried all sorts of food here, would suggest the sandwiches but not the pasta (overcooked). They have a large selection of desserts, but stay away from their chocolate chip cookies -- too crunchy for my taste. One thing I don't like is it's very hard to tell where the line is for the station you're at, people are standing around everywhere waiting for their food, so it seems a bit chaotic. I think they should do something about it. Seating is usually at a premium during the busy lunch hour, so I usually try to come a little early to beat the rush or take it to go.

Bring your own coffee mug and save a buck or so.  This place has multiple food stations. Sandwiches, pizzas, etc. I'm partial to their breakfast. They'll make omelets and such for ~ $8 with potatoes. The oatmeal is pretty good too.

A lot of choices. It wasn't too busy when I went there. They have different stations where you can get food. Pick up a tray and walk up and make your selection. I had 2 half sandwiches and a bag of chips. I had never been there before and wasn't familiar with how they were laid out. I picked the #1 Amalfi and #5 Milano. However they made me a #5 and a #8. They tasted fine, but the #1 is a vegetarian and the #8 a meat. Not a problem for me, other than I wanted the vegetarian, but that could have been a big problem for a vegetarian.

I had a fantastic experience with Sopraffina. I used them to cater 10 events for me within a week period and they executed beautifully. Sopraffina was on time, provided tasty food (said my clients), and were very easy to work with. I worked with Tim predominantly, but each staff member was able to assist. I recommend them as a catering option and will be using them again when back in town.

Really not a fan of this place. Called in with a lunch order and when I came by to pick it up, it wasn't even ready. What's the point of calling ahead then? It was a simple salad, and four people who walked up to the counter to order salads got their salads faster than me. Why didn't they just have someone at the front make it for me rather than have me wait for someone specifically in the back to make it?  No apologies or anything. When I complained about having to wait when I pre-ordered it, all I got were blank stares. Definitely not going back there.
